ctu.nengoros.comm.nodeFactory

Class NodeGroup

  • java.lang.Object
    • ctu.nengoros.comm.nodeFactory.NodeGroup

  • public class NodeGroup
extends java.lang.Object
    Group of nodes typically corresponds to one smart neuron. Communication in the group can be shielded by own, automatically generated, namespace, so that all complete node names are unique. This is handled by NameProvider and it should block the communication over the ROS network across the ROS nodes. If you want to specify absolute path, set the variable independent to false. The NameProvider then will change the names of nodes in a way that they will be unique in the ROS network, namespace if the nodes will remain unchanged. Each group has min. 0, max. 1 modem, encoders and decoders (terminations and origins on Nengo side) can be added to each modem.
